headline: From the Château de Versailles to the Elysée, the unshakable Catherine Pégard
description: Against all odds and well beyond her legal term, the former journalist who became adviser to President Nicolas Sarkozy held on as head of the Château de Versailles for 12 years. Forced out of her position in 2024, the skillful and tenacious Catherine Pégard quickly found a seat at the Elysée as culture adviser. Now, rumors suggest she could replace Rachida Dati, currently running for Paris City Hall, if she gives up her ministerial post.

UK police say ex-prince Andrew 'released under investigation'
description: The younger brother of Britain's King Charles was arrested earlier Thursday on suspicion of misconduct during his time as a trade envoy. New revelations appeared to show Andrew sent convicted US sex offender Jeffrey Epstein potentially confidential documents.

headline: USA's Alysa Liu wins the gold in Olympic women's figure skating
description: The 20-year-old put the US women back on top of the Olympic women's podium in this event for the first time since Sarah Hughes took gold at the 2002 Salt Lake City Games.

headline: In Dhaka, Sheikh Hasani's palace has been turned into a museum honoring victims of the July 2024 uprising
description: At the center of the vast property in front of the entrance, a monument has been erected in memory of all the victims of the 'Iron Lady's' regime. The museum is set to open to the public in the coming weeks.

headline: Tom Fletcher: 'Anyone who says the UN is dead should spend some time with my colleagues in Sudan or DRC'
description: The United Nations under-secretary-general for humanitarian affairs defends the role of United Nations agencies in global crises and calls for unhindered access to the Gaza Strip.

France's 13,335 millionaires who pay no income tax
description: In 2024, thousands of taxpayers with significant real estate wealth paid no income tax, according to a previously unpublished note from the Finance Ministry. These revelations have reignited the debate over taxing the country's wealthiest.

headline: Epstein scandal divides the MAGA world and weakens Trump
description: Since the latest release of files on the sexual predator, supporters of the US president have questioned the administration's lack of transparency and confusing communication.

headline: Who was Quentin Deranque, the far-right activist killed in Lyon?
description: The 23-year-old activist, who died on Saturday, February 14, after a fight in the streets of Lyon, was an integralist Catholic drawn to the idea of 'self-defense' who embodied the new generation of France's far right.
